text: Elsenfeld is a market community in the Miltenberg district in the Lower Franconia region in Bavaria, Germany. It is on the river Main between the hills of the Spessart, east of the river, and Odenwald, west of the river. Elsenfeld has about 9,000 people living there. ==Geography== ===Place=== Elsenfeld is in the "Bavarian Lower Main Region" (Bayerischer Untermain) on the Main's right edge.
